{"folder":null,"name":"Social Skills - Critical Success","img":"icons/magic/control/mouth-smile-deception-purple.webp","description":"<section class=\"secret\" id=\"secret-2aJq8AIWSOjigSIc\"><p>Includes skills such as Animal Handling, Deception, Insight, Intimidation, Performance, and Persuasion.</p><p><em><strong>Special:</strong></em> When using a disguise kit, the effect of the natural 20 or natural 1 is “stored” until a particularly opportune or inopportune time.</p></section>","results":[{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false,"_id":"S5ed4ySmqFnt28eQ","text":"Improve the target's attitude toward you—someone that was put off might become apathetic, and an apathetic person might become friendly.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Clever Banter"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false,"_id":"wAMBj3k0ymGwwBpI","text":"The target calls over some friends that are friendly to you and interested in what you are doing.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Friendly Crowd"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false,"_id":"XztrWwtJEmUD3sSM","text":"The target wants to give you some small gift outside the scope of this conversation.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Gift"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false,"_id":"jmExHZvvqPhXAlA0","text":"After this conversation, the attitudes of the target's closest allies improve towards you (as Clever Banter).","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Good Reputation"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false,"_id":"1XNUJv1lH1hhdUU1","text":"The target accidentally reveals a useful piece of information.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Loose lips"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false,"_id":"kwPq4MgkyfSSg1lt","text":"The target may become romantically interested with you.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Love Interest"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"}],"replacement":true,"displayRoll":false,"flags":{},"formula":"1d6","_id":"vmf9w8gtsdi2h45n"}
{"folder":null,"name":"Social Skills - Critical Failure","img":"icons/magic/control/mouth-smile-deception-purple.webp","description":"<section class=\"secret\" id=\"secret-iocoL0XUTiOWLmTK\"><p>Includes skills such as Animal Handling, Deception, Insight, Intimidation, Performance, and Persuasion.</p><p><em><strong>Special:</strong></em> When using a disguise kit, the effect of the natural 20 or natural 1 is “stored” until a particularly opportune or inopportune time.</p></section>","results":[{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false,"_id":"S5ed4ySmqFnt28eQ","text":"You accidentally reveal a piece of information best kept hidden.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Accidental Reveal"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false,"_id":"wAMBj3k0ymGwwBpI","text":"The target calls over some friends that are not fans of you and your cause.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Escalating Tension"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false,"_id":"XztrWwtJEmUD3sSM","text":"You believe something truthful that the target says to be a lie.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"False Negative"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false,"_id":"jmExHZvvqPhXAlA0","text":"After this conversation, the attitudes of the target's close allies worsen towards you. Someone who was apathetic might be put off, and someone put off might become borderline hostile.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Gossip"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false,"_id":"1XNUJv1lH1hhdUU1","text":"The target believes something truthful to be a lie.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Suspicious"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false,"_id":"kwPq4MgkyfSSg1lt","text":"Worsen the target's attitude toward you by one step (as Gossip).","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Unfriendly Banter"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"}],"replacement":true,"displayRoll":false,"flags":{},"formula":"1d6","_id":"3m0vyh75nnlj42ja"}
{"folder":null,"name":"Physical Skills - Critical Success","img":"icons/magic/control/buff-strength-muscle-damage-orange.webp","description":"<section class=\"secret\" id=\"secret-mi255rlk9heooBKb\"><p>Includes skills such as Acrobatics, Athletics, Sleight of Hand, and Stealth.</p></section>","results":[{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false,"_id":"S5ed4ySmqFnt28eQ","text":"For the next 24 hours, when making a skill check of the same type, you can choose to gain a result as if you had rolled a 10 on the die instead of rolling.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Cool Confidence"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false,"_id":"wAMBj3k0ymGwwBpI","text":"You impress others with your physical feat. For the next hour, you gain an expertise die on Intimidation and Persuasion checks against targets who saw your success.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Impressive Success"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false,"_id":"XztrWwtJEmUD3sSM","text":"Your allies who attempt a similar check in the next 5 minutes gain an expertise die.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Lead the Way"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false,"_id":"jmExHZvvqPhXAlA0","text":"For the next hour, you ignore any disadvantage to Stealth checks gained from wearing armor.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Like Wearing Nothing at All"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false,"_id":"1XNUJv1lH1hhdUU1","text":"You'll sleep well tonight. For the next 24 hours, double the hit points you regain from spending Hit Dice during a short rest.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Satisfying Exhaustion"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false,"_id":"kwPq4MgkyfSSg1lt","text":"You can immediately use your reaction to move half your Speed.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Speedy"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"}],"replacement":true,"displayRoll":false,"flags":{},"formula":"1d6","_id":"8q8hhm2qxxpzqety"}
{"folder":null,"name":"Physical Skills - Critical Failure","img":"icons/magic/control/buff-strength-muscle-damage-orange.webp","description":"<section class=\"secret\" id=\"secret-8gvHBAYdWBJqQzzV\"><p>Includes skills such as Acrobatics, Athletics, Sleight of Hand, and Stealth.</p></section>","results":[{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false,"_id":"S5ed4ySmqFnt28eQ","text":"An item held in your hands (Narrator's choice) gains the broken condition.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Fumble"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false,"_id":"wAMBj3k0ymGwwBpI","text":"You jam your fingers or toes, and for the next 10 minutes your melee attack bonus or AC are reduced by –1 (Narrator's choice).","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Jam"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false,"_id":"XztrWwtJEmUD3sSM","text":"Something you are wearing inexplicably gains the broken condition (Narrator's choice).","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Loosened Latch"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false,"_id":"jmExHZvvqPhXAlA0","text":"You fall prone.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Off Balance"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false,"_id":"1XNUJv1lH1hhdUU1","text":"Your Speed is reduced by 5 feet for the next hour.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Pull a Ligament"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false,"_id":"kwPq4MgkyfSSg1lt","text":"You suffer 2 levels of fatigue. After 1 round one of these levels of fatigue is removed, and the other is gone after 1 hour.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Pushed Too Hard"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"}],"replacement":true,"displayRoll":false,"flags":{},"formula":"1d6","_id":"sckaut8fmaq8l120"}
{"folder":null,"name":"Medicine - Critical Success","img":"icons/skills/wounds/injury-stitched-flesh-red.webp","description":"","results":[{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false,"_id":"S5ed4ySmqFnt28eQ","text":"The target gains a number of temporary hit points equal to your proficiency bonus. These temporary hit points last 1 hour.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Buffer"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false,"_id":"wAMBj3k0ymGwwBpI","text":"The target heals 1 level of fatigue or strife (reroll if neither applies).","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Comprehensive Checkup"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false,"_id":"XztrWwtJEmUD3sSM","text":"For the next 24 hours, when making Medicine checks, you can choose to gain a result as if you had rolled a 10 on the die instead of rolling.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Expertise"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false,"_id":"jmExHZvvqPhXAlA0","text":"You may treat your next Medicine check as a natural 20 so long as it is made before you complete a long rest. This does not result in a critical success.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Repeat the Procedure"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false,"_id":"1XNUJv1lH1hhdUU1","text":"The target's natural healing improves dramatically. For the next 24 hours, double the hit points the target regains from spending Hit Dice during a short rest.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Spur Natural Healing"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false,"_id":"kwPq4MgkyfSSg1lt","text":"The target regains additional hit points equal to your proficiency bonus.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Superb Healing"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"}],"replacement":true,"displayRoll":false,"flags":{},"formula":"1d6","_id":"66wtmckaxsjl2cay"}
{"folder":null,"name":"Medicine - Critical Failure","img":"icons/skills/wounds/injury-stitched-flesh-red.webp","description":"","results":[{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false,"_id":"S5ed4ySmqFnt28eQ","text":"You accidentally amputate the patient's little toe (or similar non-vital extremity). Now, how did you do that?","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Amputate Toe"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false,"_id":"wAMBj3k0ymGwwBpI","text":"You and the target are poisoned for 1 minute.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Disgusting Procedure"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false,"_id":"XztrWwtJEmUD3sSM","text":"The target takes [[1d4]] bludgeoning, piercing, or slashing damage.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Harm"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false,"_id":"jmExHZvvqPhXAlA0","text":"The target must make a DC 12 Constitution saving throw or becomes infected with sewer plague.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Infect Wound"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false,"_id":"1XNUJv1lH1hhdUU1","text":"The target takes 1 ongoing damage for 1 minute. Each turn the target can use its bonus action to make a Constitution saving throw (DC 20 – 1 per previous save) to stop the bleeding. Any amount of magical healing also stops the bleeding.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Open Wound"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false,"_id":"kwPq4MgkyfSSg1lt","text":"The target suffers one level of fatigue.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Organ Damage"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"}],"replacement":true,"displayRoll":false,"flags":{},"formula":"1d6","_id":"ihsspmdmmpj8cyk8"}
{"folder":null,"name":"Facts and Discoveries - Critical Success","img":"icons/sundries/scrolls/scroll-writing-brown-gold.webp","description":"<section class=\"secret\" id=\"secret-LMW17rh8yFe05R43\"><p>Includes skills such as Arcana, Culture, Engineering, History, Investigation, Nature, Perception, Religion, and Survival.</p></section>","results":[{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false,"_id":"S5ed4ySmqFnt28eQ","text":"<b>Doctorate</b><br />This subject is one of your areas of study and some of it is coming back to you. For the next 24 hours, you gain an expertise die on ability checks using this skill so long as the check is for similar subjects.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Doctorate"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false,"_id":"wAMBj3k0ymGwwBpI","text":"Choose the language most closely associated with the target (if none or if you already know the language, roll again). If this is your first time getting a critical success with that language, you remember that you studied it long ago. Write down the language. The next time you roll this result, you permanently learn the language.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Forgotten Language"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false,"_id":"XztrWwtJEmUD3sSM","text":"You gain the benefits of a single <i>augury</i> spell (although no magic is involved).","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Moment of Revelations"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false,"_id":"jmExHZvvqPhXAlA0","text":"For the next hour, you may add half your proficiency bonus to any Intelligence or Wisdom check that doesn’t already include your proficiency bonus.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Related Expertise"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false,"_id":"1XNUJv1lH1hhdUU1","text":"You recall some important bit of information relevant to the target.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Relevant Tidbit"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false,"_id":"kwPq4MgkyfSSg1lt","text":"For 1 minute, you gain the benefits of <i>detect magic</i> against targets related to your check.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"View Auras"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"}],"replacement":true,"displayRoll":false,"flags":{},"formula":"1d6","_id":"27u8uhi0v7x4dxwz"}
{"folder":null,"name":"Facts and Discoveries - Critical Failure","img":"icons/sundries/scrolls/scroll-writing-brown-gold.webp","description":"<section id=\"secret-FJrPfH2aBJVHV3ee\" class=\"secret\"><p>Includes skills such as Arcana, Culture, Engineering, History, Investigation, Nature, Perception, Religion, and Survival.</p></section>","results":[{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false,"_id":"S5ed4ySmqFnt28eQ","text":"If you are examining something, you either break it or worsen a creature’s attitude towards you (as Gossip, page 416). When this does not apply, reroll.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Aggressive Handling"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false,"_id":"wAMBj3k0ymGwwBpI","text":"You lose one of your highest level spell slots. When this does not apply, reroll.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Arcane Fatigue"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false,"_id":"XztrWwtJEmUD3sSM","text":"You find this topic incredibly boring. For the next 24 hours, you take a –2 penalty on checks against similar targets.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Boring Topic"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false,"_id":"jmExHZvvqPhXAlA0","text":"You are trying to concentrate but all you can remember is an annoying tune. For the next hour, you cannot gain expertise dice on Intelligence and Wisdom checks.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Earworm"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false,"_id":"1XNUJv1lH1hhdUU1","text":"You become frightened for [[1d4+1]] rounds. There is no direct source of your fear.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Frightening Revelation"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false,"_id":"kwPq4MgkyfSSg1lt","text":"You are positive of the veracity of some false bit of information.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Misinformation"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"}],"replacement":true,"displayRoll":false,"flags":{},"formula":"1d6","_id":"jbjp515vtjmolbng"}
{"folder":null,"name":"Arcane - Critical Success","img":"icons/magic/symbols/runes-star-pentagon-orange-purple.webp","description":"<section class=\"secret\" id=\"secret-t1OpHwA8LRQSiK48\"><p>Arcane criticals only occur when an active magical effect is involved. This might be the response to a <em>counterspell</em> or <em>dispel magic</em>, the activation of a specific magic item, or interaction with a ritual or permanent enchantment. When an arcane critical success or critical failure would not apply to the effect that activated it, reroll.</p></section>","results":[{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false,"_id":"S5ed4ySmqFnt28eQ","text":"You gain temporary hit points equal to your proficiency bonus. These temporary hit points last 1 hour.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Arcane Surge"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false,"_id":"wAMBj3k0ymGwwBpI","text":"You may take 10 on Arcana checks for the next 24 hours, even if it is not normally allowed.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Comfort in the Arcane"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false,"_id":"XztrWwtJEmUD3sSM","text":"If the magic item or effect targets a set number of targets, you may add one additional target within range.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Expanded Use"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false,"_id":"jmExHZvvqPhXAlA0","text":"If activating a scroll or item with charges (such as a wand), you do not use the scroll or any charges.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Free Use"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false,"_id":"1XNUJv1lH1hhdUU1","text":"You gain an expertise die on Arcana checks for the next 24 hours.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Lucky Magic"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false,"_id":"kwPq4MgkyfSSg1lt","text":"Choose one minor metamagic from those found in the sorcerer class and apply it to the spell.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Metamagic Use"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"}],"replacement":true,"displayRoll":false,"flags":{},"formula":"1d6","_id":"1hwn0mlv5yjte3i0"}
{"folder":null,"name":"Arcane - Critical Failure","img":"icons/magic/symbols/runes-star-pentagon-orange-purple.webp","description":"<section class=\"secret\" id=\"secret-OETdyuPqGqKT4iiZ\"><p>Arcane criticals only occur when an active magical effect is involved. This might be the response to a <em>counterspell</em> or <em>dispel magic</em>, the activation of a specific magic item, or interaction with a ritual or permanent enchantment. When an arcane critical success or critical failure would not apply to the effect that activated it, reroll.</p></section>","results":[{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false,"_id":"S5ed4ySmqFnt28eQ","text":"You take 1 point of damage per spell level.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Arcane Feedback"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false,"_id":"wAMBj3k0ymGwwBpI","text":"The activated item gains the broken condition or, in the case of a scroll it is destroyed entirely.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Break Device"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false,"_id":"XztrWwtJEmUD3sSM","text":"At some point within the next [[1d12]] hours, the magic device randomly activates. The target is chosen by the Narrator.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Delayed Activation"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false,"_id":"jmExHZvvqPhXAlA0","text":"The device activates, but the target of the item's effect or spell changes to a target of the Narrator's choosing.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Misaligned Aiming"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false,"_id":"1XNUJv1lH1hhdUU1","text":"You are rattled for the next [[2d4]] hours.","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Unlucky Magic"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"},{"type":0,"weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false,"_id":"kwPq4MgkyfSSg1lt","text":"If activating an item with charges (such as a wand), you use 5 charges (even if the device does not activate).","documentId":null,"flags":{"title":"Wasteful Usage"},"img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg"}],"replacement":true,"displayRoll":false,"flags":{},"formula":"1d6","_id":"7j24frcbj7xy0iby"}
